The article discusses the importance of mitigating insider threats in nuclear and radiological security. It mentions that insiders, due to their access rights and knowledge, pose a greater threat than outsiders. The article suggests establishing national-level measures, policies, and programs to mitigate these threats. It also emphasizes the need for training and awareness activities, collaboration between organizations, and strong control and accountability measures for special nuclear material. The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) is mentioned as developing advanced training courses on preventive and protective measures against insider threats. The article also mentions the development of a nuclear security regime, including physical protection systems, trustworthiness programs, and cyber hygiene procedures. Insider trustworthiness programs may include background checks, vetting of personnel, psychological testing, and security awareness training.